The paper deals with the complexity of cryptographic primitives and their connections to polynomial pigeonhole principle (PPP), which is a topic closely related to computational complexity and cryptography. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses lattice-based problems, which are a topic in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The construction of a hash function family also involves topics in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
